text: So sad to see great actors (Matthew McConaughey and Anne Hathaway) letting their performance standards (acting and choice of films) plummet to such new lows.  The acting was laughable.  Hathaway barely showed up for this movie, while McConaughey was perfectly content falling back on his standard repertoire of drunken grimaces and looney laughs.  His level of self absorption on the other hand hit an all time high in this movie where there is little doubt that the order of the day was to keep the camera focused on his naked body.  I mean, sex scenes with Anne Hathaway and Dianne Lane and all you ever see is McCaunoghey's bare but!  I'm not kidding!  Honestly, the 19% rating on the Rotten Tomatoes Tomatometer quite generous to this movie!!

text: I just watched this, tonight, May 5th.  Certainly one of the more original and entirely different stories I've ever seen. As soon as I saw the POV of the son, and what he was doing, I knew completely what the story was trying to say. And it was well done. Most people expected a simple murder thriller, but this goes exponents beyond that myopic frame. It's really difficult for unique storylines to make a financial grounding in today's cookie cutter action/comedy/superhero environment, but I'm glad there are movies like this one. It moved my heart in a way I didn't expect. Alas, the hypocrisy of the masses screaming for new and original movies, then lamenting the very originality they said they wanted.
